com.launchdarkly.sdk.collections

Class IterableAsyncQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.launchdarkly.sdk.collections.IterableAsyncQueue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements held in this queue

    public class IterableAsyncQueue<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    A thread-safe unbounded queue that provides asynchronous consumption via CompletableFuture.

    This queue supports multiple concurrent producers and consumers. Items are delivered in FIFO order. The take() method returns a CompletableFuture that either completes immediately if an item is available, or completes later when an item is added via put(Object).

    When multiple consumers are waiting (i.e., multiple pending take() calls), they are satisfied in FIFO order as items become available.

    Null values are supported.

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put(T item)
        Adds an item to the queue.

        If there is a consumer is waiting (a pending take() call), the item is delivered directly to the oldest waiting consumer's future. Otherwise, the item is added to the queue for later consumption.

        If a future returned by this method is completed or canceled by the caller, then the item associated with that call will not be delivered. It is recommended not to complete or cancel the future returned by take() unless you are finished using the queue.

        Parameters:
        item - the item to add (maybe null)

      • take

        public java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<T> take()
        Retrieves and removes an item from the queue, returning a future that completes with the item.

        If the queue contains items, returns an already-completed future with the oldest item. If the queue is empty, returns a future that will complete when an item becomes available via put(Object).

        Returns:
        a CompletableFuture that completes with the next item
